      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You absolutely should NOT stop using your inhaler, as doing so could lead to a severe asthma attack and even death. Taking a double dose of your salbutamol is dangerous and can cause life-threatening side effects like dangerous heart rhythms or seizures. You must see a doctor immediately to get your asthma properly managed, but if you cannot go to the ER right now, please call your local emergency number (911) for guidance on the safest way to get help.",
